## 3. Execute Batch

### 3.1 Select Batch Issues

```
BASED ON strategy:

IF by-file:
  SELECT 2-4 files with most issues

IF by-rule:
  SELECT 1-2 related rules (~20 occurrences max)

IF by-folder:
  SELECT issues in target folder (~20 max)

PRESENT batch to human:

**BATCH [N] - [count] ISSUES**

Strategy: [by-file | by-rule | folder]

**Scope:** [files/rules/folder details]

**Issues:**
1. `[file:line]` - [rule] - [message]
2. `[file:line]` - [rule] - [message]
...

Executing via /midtempo-framework/refactor.md

PROCEED to §3.2
```

### 3.2 Execute Using Refactor Skill

```
FOLLOW /midtempo-framework/refactor.md EXACTLY:

1. ENTRY GATE (from refactor.md)
   - Verify tests are green before starting
   - If tests not green → STOP, fix tests first

2. FOR each lint issue:

   ANALYSE the violation:
   - Read full file context
   - Understand what the code does
   - Identify refactor approach

   APPLY refactor patterns:

   IF function too long:
     → Extract logical sections into helper functions
     → Each helper has single responsibility
     → Names describe what, not how

   IF complexity too high:
     → Simplify conditionals (guard clauses, early returns)
     → Extract conditional logic to named functions
     → Reduce nesting depth

   IF file too long:
     → Split by responsibility
     → Extract cohesive modules
     → Maintain clear boundaries

   IF too many parameters:
     → Group related params into objects
     → Consider builder pattern
     → Review if function does too much

   VERIFY after each change:
     → Tests still pass
     → Behaviour unchanged
     → Lint issue resolved
     → No new issues introduced

3. EXIT GATE (from refactor.md)
   - All tests green
   - Behaviour unchanged
   - Metrics improved (lint issues reduced)

IMPORTANT - DO NOT:
  - Add eslint-disable comments
  - Disable rules
  - Make functional changes (only structural)
  - Create meaningless helper functions just to reduce line count
```

### 3.3 Verify Batch

```
AFTER all batch fixes applied:

RUN: {{ "lint" | cmd }}
RUN: {{ test_gate(this) }}

VERIFY:
  - Batch issues resolved
  - No new lint issues
  - All tests pass

IF tests fail
  → STOP
  → Fix immediately
  → Tests MUST pass before proceeding

IF new lint issues introduced
  → Fix immediately (same batch)
  → Re-verify
```

